	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Are you sure EIST is responsible for the problem?  RMClock will show you what capabilities the processor has, and which ones are actually in use (CPU-Z doesn't do this).
<br />
<br />EIST works surprisingly well, and given that, usually "choppy performance" means ACPI-based clock throttling is being used instead.  RMClock can help determine this as well, I believe.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


